      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks. I'm curious about the \"demographic shifts\" part though. When you talk about the high-density area having higher risk because of the churn and shifting demographics, are you implying that the change in the actual makeup of the population is what makes it unstable for investors? Like, does a more diverse or changing population inherently make property values more volatile compared to the established area?",
